      • parseMaterialDefinition

        public static MaterialDefinition parseMaterialDefinition(String value)
                                                  throws IllegalArgumentException
        Parses MaterialDefinitions from a string.
        Accepts the following:
        • Names defined in items.csv
        • minecraft id. eg. minecraft:stone
        • bukkit material. eg. STONE
        Except when using a name from items.csv, you may include a data value after the id. eg 'STONE:2' or 'minecraft:stone:2'
        Parameters:
        value - The string to parse
        Returns:
        The parsed MaterialDefinition
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - Thrown if the value cannot be parsed as a material

      • parseItemStack

        public static org.bukkit.inventory.ItemStack parseItemStack(String value)
                                                     throws IllegalArgumentException
        Parse an ItemStack from a string.
        The expected format is '{count}x{type}'
        Count must be a positive integer, type will be parsed with parseMaterialDefinition(String)
        Parameters:
        value - The string to parse
        Returns:
        The parsed ItemStack
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - Thrown if the value could not be parsed

      • parse

        public static <T> T parse(Class<T> type,
                          String value)
                   throws IllegalArgumentException,
                          UnsupportedOperationException
        A generic parse method which attempts to parse the value based on what type you want out.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The class that defines the Type you wish to return
        Parameters:
        type - The type you want to get
        value - The value to parse
        Returns:
        An instance of the specified type with a value equivalent to the input string
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - Thrown if an error occurs while parsing the value
        UnsupportedOperationException - Thrown if the specified type cant be parsed by this method
